= lesson 4: adjectives

== Describe!
Now you know some nouns (things) and verbs (actions). Time to add adjectives
(descriptions)! \
Let's memorise a few of them:

#list((
  word("ůĪ•£", "suli", "large, important"),
  word("ůĪ§®", "lili", "small, young"),
  word("ůĪ•Ď", "pona", "good, pleasant"),
  word("ůĪ•Ē", "ike", "bad, unpleasant"),
  word("ůĪ•Ķ", "wawa", "powerful, amazing"),
  word("ůĪ•°", "sona", "knowledgeable, wise"),
  word("ůĪ•¶", "suwi", "cute, sweet"),
))

In English, adjectives go before the noun. But in Toki Pona, they always go
after:
#list((
  word("ůĪ•ĘůĪ•£", "soweli suli", "a large animal"),
  word("ůĪ•ĎůĪ§®", "pipi lili", "a small bug"),
  word("ůĪ•īůĪ•¶", "waso suwi", "an adorable bird"),
))

English speakers sometimes find this order confusing, but this order is normal
in French, Irish, Arabic, Malay, and many other languages. Think of it this way:
the first word is always the most important!

